Dialogue: 1,0:00:51.90,0:00:54.86,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}I want to be annoying for you
Dialogue: 1,0:00:54.86,0:00:57.82,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}I don't mind being conceited
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.82,0:01:01.87,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}Hide a tree in a forest, they say
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.62,0:01:06.37,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}It started with a little mistake
Dialogue: 1,0:01:06.37,0:01:09.38,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}Let's redo our meeting from there
Dialogue: 1,0:01:09.38,0:01:13.84,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}Let's oppose the strand of time
Dialogue: 1,0:01:14.59,0:01:19.80,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}Strength alone is no weapon
Dialogue: 1,0:01:20.89,0:01:27.98,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}You taught me that just now
Dialogue: 1,0:01:27.98,0:01:33.48,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}I want to show you what lies
Dialogue: 1,0:01:33.48,0:01:39.70,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}beyond these days
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.70,0:01:42.24,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}The wind is strong
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.24,0:01:45.33,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}I'm sure you know that too
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.33,0:01:50.17,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}I can't fly
Dialogue: 1,0:01:51.17,0:01:56.97,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}Sharing makes you dependant
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.97,0:02:00.14,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}Now, take my hand
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.14,0:02:02.68,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}Hold it tight
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.68,0:02:06.98,OP,bord,0,0,0,done,{\blur3\fad(100,100)}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.85,0:02:13.78,Titles,,0,0,0,,{\c&H61CFFA&\blur0.6\shad2\4c&H000E13&\pos(492.857,100.096)} Chapter 10
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.85,0:02:13.78,Titles,,0,0,0,,{\c&H64DAFC&\blur0.6\shad2\4c&H000E13&\pos(743.143,425.714)} So now their plans are \Nfinally coming to fruition?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.74,0:02:16.78,Default,Queen,0,0,0,,We'll have to free the serfs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.39,0:02:20.07,Default,Queen,0,0,0,,We should stand with the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.31,0:02:24.08,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,The potatoes have doubled the population we can support.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.58,0:02:25.92,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,It's true we could...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.92,0:02:30.08,Default,Fm,0,0,0,,But that'd be an act of outright defiance against the Central Nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.04,0:02:33.67,Default,Fm,0,0,0,,A war against them would wipe us out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.99,0:02:37.47,Default,OtherAdvisor,0,0,0,,If I may, I doubt they'd attack immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:39.35,Default,OtherAdvisor,0,0,0,,Should they destroy us,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.35,0:02:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they'd lose the buffer protecting them from the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.56,0:02:43.43,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.76,0:02:48.84,Default,OA,0,0,0,,And their military force is divided among numerous local lords.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.84,0:02:50.43,Default,OA,0,0,0,,Uniting them would take at least six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.08,0:02:51.81,Default,Y,0,0,0,,I can't accept this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.11,0:02:55.36,Default,K,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:02:58.78,Default,Y,0,0,0,,I don't understand this anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.38,0:03:02.12,Default,Y,0,0,0,,What exactly do the Central Nations,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.51,0:03:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe the church or the king,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.04,0:03:05.62,Default,Y,0,0,0,,hope to accomplish?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.07,0:03:15.12,Default,K,0,0,0,,To unite the entire world beneath the banner of the Holy Light.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.12,0:03:16.80,Default,K,0,0,0,,A noble cause,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.15,0:03:20.59,Default,K,0,0,0,,but in truth, they covet the wealth of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.11,0:03:25.14,Default,K,0,0,0,,But wealth isn't enough. They also want knowledge, respect, and power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.14,0:03:27.81,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,By stealing from others within a closed system,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.81,0:03:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they can create a stratified society, with themselves firmly at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.86,0:03:33.48,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,That's the society they'd like to perpetuate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.21,0:03:37.86,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,Isn't that why the whole world will never be prosperous?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.63,0:03:40.70,Default,Y,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.99,0:03:43.87,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,Milady once told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.32,0:03:47.81,Default,M,0,0,0,,Keeping all the wealth for yourself may make you rich,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.81,0:03:49.37,Default,M,0,0,0,,but it won't make you prosperous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.60,0:03:51.69,Default,M,0,0,0,,You give people money, and they spend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.51,0:03:57.38,Default,M,0,0,0,,True prosperity comes from a free flow of wealth and goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.78,0:03:59.12,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.31,0:04:02.82,Default,K,0,0,0,,So to maintain their wealth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.82,0:04:06.35,Default,K,0,0,0,,the church impoverishes everyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.07,0:04:11.13,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Then what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.67,0:04:15.52,Default,Y,0,0,0,,What must happen for this to improve?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.28,0:04:20.90,Default,Ms,0,0,0,,When you don't know what to do, enjoy some dessert!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.31,0:04:24.24,Default,Ms,0,0,0,,I have strawberry pie and pear pie!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.24,0:04:27.04,Default,Ms,0,0,0,,There're two, so pick what you like!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.83,0:04:33.92,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,The Lakeside Convent really did that?{prolly insert a 'yes' or something after this?}{blank line timed, but if not used just delete it}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.92,0:04:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.88,0:04:36.29,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,They've established a new church.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.29,0:04:39.34,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,They call it the "True Church of the Holy Light."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.34,0:04:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They're making it the national religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.46,0:04:46.81,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.16,0:04:50.43,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,I did {\i1}not{\i0} see that coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.43,0:04:52.88,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,That couldn't've been her, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.62,0:04:55.85,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,She'd never do something so rash.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.13,0:05:01.58,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,The Hero, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.83,0:05:06.50,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,Chairman...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.50,0:05:08.73,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,That's seriously brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.35,0:05:14.88,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,Apparently, the Central Church is in chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.88,0:05:19.19,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,Still, it's unlikely their support for the Central Church will waver.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.19,0:05:20.84,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,But what interests me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.34,0:05:27.08,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,The liberation of the serfs?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.98,0:05:30.26,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,This isn't parchment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:34.60,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,But unlike papyrus, it's sturdy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.23,0:05:38.10,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,And the letters seemed to have been stamped into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.34,0:05:42.57,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,Papers identical to these are being widely distributed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.87,0:05:44.87,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,At least 3,000 or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.87,0:05:47.57,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Three thousand of these?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.71,0:05:52.37,Default,M,0,0,0,,To aid the arid regions within the Central Nations,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.63,0:05:55.92,Default,M,0,0,0,,I've developed a far more effective method than the waterwheel,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.98,0:06:00.36,Default,M,0,0,0,,as well as something to write on that'll replace parchment forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.70,0:06:08.03,Default,M,0,0,0,,So now their plans are finally coming to fruition?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.61,0:06:12.76,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,How is the council leaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.14,0:06:16.16,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,Three back the Central, and two the Southern Triad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.16,0:06:17.77,Default,Accountant,0,0,0,,The rest remain neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.13,0:06:20.93,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Locate their assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.93,0:06:21.69,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.77,0:06:24.07,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,What's happened to wheat prices?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.07,0:06:25.19,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Up by two points.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.60,0:06:28.93,Default,Account,0,0,0,,The Central Nations' economic recession is raising prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.93,0:06:32.20,Default,Account,0,0,0,,If we sell our current stock, we'll make quite a profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.37,0:06:34.40,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,No, we should buy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.40,0:06:35.45,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Buy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.88,0:06:40.33,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Iron ingots, charcoal, silver: Buy all of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.50,0:06:41.81,Default,Account,0,0,0,,How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.81,0:06:44.84,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,As much as you can without raising suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.84,0:06:47.39,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Buy wheat at 100 points until next week
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.39,0:06:50.81,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,and up to 250 until the end of next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.11,0:06:54.56,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,We'll fill this place up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.17,0:06:57.43,Default,Account,0,0,0,,I've never heard of anyone buying at those prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.97,0:07:00.90,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Buying wheat isn't our objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.34,0:07:04.30,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,It's to sell currency.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.47,0:07:08.28,Default,General,0,0,0,,Twelve more entered the country yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.66,0:07:11.47,Default,General,0,0,0,,This makes 218.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.88,0:07:15.79,Default,Y,0,0,0,,I thought there'd be more.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.92,0:07:19.04,Default,Queen,0,0,0,,A song, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.35,0:07:23.27,Default,Queen,0,0,0,,Songs can teach even
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.27,0:07:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult words to illiterate peasants.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.41,0:07:30.50,Default,Queen,0,0,0,,My kingdom is the Bard Country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.50,0:07:34.35,Default,Queen,0,0,0,,If we compensate them for singing of our new teachings...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.71,0:07:35.30,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.31,0:07:38.50,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,Won't the church denounce
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.50,0:07:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone who spreads our teachings?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.26,0:07:44.61,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,Won't they brand them liars or demonic thralls?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.14,0:07:47.21,Default,K,0,0,0,,It's the only trick those idiots know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.69,0:07:52.34,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,I don't think we should do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.34,0:07:56.37,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,Most of their followers are simple believers of the Holy Light.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.01,0:08:01.29,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,No good will come of involving them in an ugly fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.24,0:08:06.17,Default,Queen,0,0,0,,Then how should we get more people here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.56,0:08:09.13,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,We explain why they should come.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.68,0:08:12.98,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,The southern lands are wild, and it'll be difficult,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.98,0:08:15.04,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,but there {\i1}is{\i0} hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.04,0:08:16.77,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,There's no serfdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.77,0:08:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone who works hard will be rewarded,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.12,0:08:21.63,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,and taxes are very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.21,0:08:26.77,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,The Light afforded us this opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.77,0:08:28.48,Default,Mb,0,0,0,,If the bards spread such songs,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.81,0:08:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't that bring a lot of people?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.69,0:08:39.54,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,I thought you were going to say something idealistic,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.99,0:08:43.48,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,but that's actually an accurate assessment of our situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.98,0:08:46.46,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,How's the market responding?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.66,0:08:50.96,Default,Account,0,0,0,,The nobles and merchants are responding well, as they have wheat at hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.23,0:08:52.97,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Some of them are liquidating.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.97,0:08:55.34,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,And the farm owners?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.97,0:08:58.08,Default,Account,0,0,0,,They're becoming nervous,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.08,0:09:01.31,Default,Account,0,0,0,,but a few are willing to sell if the offer is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.31,0:09:02.40,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.92,0:09:05.35,Default,Account,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.34,0:09:07.86,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,I'll call it— Well, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.24,0:09:12.05,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,A product purchase agreement, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.05,0:09:13.69,Default,Account,0,0,0,,A purchase agreement?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.21,0:09:17.70,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,For example, this winter I would pay up front
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.82,0:09:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to purchase next year's wheat crop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.20,0:09:26.04,Default,Account,0,0,0,,So the land owners sell wheat they don't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.37,0:09:28.19,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,But when summer comes,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.19,0:09:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they must have the wheat, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.05,0:09:34.37,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,If wheat prices have risen with a bad harvest,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.37,0:09:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we can acquire the wheat at lower prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.38,0:09:39.93,Default,Account,0,0,0,,So you think the price will rise?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.93,0:09:42.23,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,With the Central calling the southern ones heretics,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.23,0:09:44.95,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,chances are good there'll be a war.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.95,0:09:47.56,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,And even if there isn't, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.97,0:09:53.57,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,As long as people want to eat it, we can artificially limit production to keep prices high.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.57,0:09:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one real goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.07,0:10:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To keep the Central Nations' nobility thinking of next year's wheat market.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.57,0:10:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Next summer comes,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.91,0:10:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and not only isn't there much wheat to sell,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.03,0:10:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,there isn't much to eat either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.46,0:10:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And suppose the prices keep increasing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.09,0:10:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need for them to rise in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.81,0:10:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All we need is for them to worry,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.47,0:10:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and that fear will make us rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.35,0:10:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We just keep issuing these agreements and handing them money.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.27,0:10:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can move the Alliance's HQ in preparation for the next step.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.43,0:10:28.61,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Out of nowhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.61,0:10:29.98,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Well, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.42,0:10:31.95,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Why not the Lake Country?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.95,0:10:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's near the Southern Triad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.71,0:10:37.82,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,And the Lakeside Convent is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.48,0:10:40.74,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,A fun dance party is about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.20,0:10:45.58,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Let's let the Central nobility enjoy a long, long winter.{winter is coming}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.91,0:10:46.50,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Buy,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.50,0:10:47.41,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,sell,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.41,0:10:49.29,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,exchange
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.29,0:10:52.83,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,until this endless waltz encompasses the entire continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.26,0:10:59.76,Default,EFG,0,0,0,,Potatoes and salt?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.07,0:11:04.18,Default,EFG,0,0,15,,The town's salt supply has run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.18,0:11:08.92,Default,Demon Merchant,0,0,15,,Losing Bright Light Island's rock salt supply hurt us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.65,0:11:12.12,Default,Princess,0,0,0,,Stop complaining,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.54,0:11:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Cloud Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.10,0:11:19.19,Default,Princess,0,0,0,,The Eastern Fortress General sides with the humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.19,0:11:22.45,Default,DM,0,0,0,,Oh, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.77,0:11:25.45,Default,EFG,0,0,0,,Don't worry. We'll think of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.80,0:11:29.91,Default,DP,0,0,0,,General, are you familiar with the Azure Demons?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.21,0:11:32.67,Default,EFG,0,0,0,,The ones with blue skin?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.67,0:11:36.56,Default,DP,0,0,0,,They're one of the Greater Races, and more Demon Kings descend from them than any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.56,0:11:41.30,Default,DP,0,0,0,,They're the ones who most desire to conquer the Human World.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.30,0:11:43.36,Default,EFG,0,0,0,,Sounds like a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.36,0:11:44.80,Default,DP,0,0,0,,There's a rumor that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.01,0:11:50.48,Default,DP,0,0,0,,they're secretly contacting humans here in Gate City.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.27,0:11:52.56,Default,Peasant,0,0,0,,Are you insane?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.79,0:11:55.44,Default,Peasant,0,0,0,,Eight silver for a bag of wheat?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.44,0:11:56.98,Default,Peasant,0,0,0,,That's twice the normal price.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.98,0:11:58.34,Default,Peasant,0,0,0,,Who would buy that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.34,0:12:00.95,Default,Wheat Merchant,0,0,0,,You haven't been shopping for a while, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.15,0:12:03.18,Default,Traveling Merchant,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.10,0:12:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How much for the grade-B wheat?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.87,0:12:07.95,Default,WM,0,0,0,,Six and a half silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.95,0:12:10.45,Default,WM,0,0,0,,It has some bugs, and isn't as finely ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.45,0:12:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's still good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.23,0:12:15.63,Default,TM,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll take 25 bags.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.63,0:12:17.17,Default,Peasant,0,0,0,,Are you crazy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.94,0:12:20.01,Default,TM,0,0,0,,Nowadays, that's cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.46,0:12:23.79,Default,Peasant,0,0,0,,I'll take the grade-B stuff, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.79,0:12:24.80,Default,WM,0,0,0,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.59,0:12:27.83,Default,WM,0,0,0,,One bag for eight and a half silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.83,0:12:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.59,0:12:30.31,Default,Peasant,0,0,0,,Wasn't it six and a half?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.31,0:12:32.73,Default,WM,0,0,0,,Didn't you see how much I just sold?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.31,0:12:36.56,Default,WM,0,0,0,,A week ago, it was four silver per bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.56,0:12:39.89,Default,WM,0,0,0,,And rumor has it that next week, it'll be fifteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.89,0:12:43.11,Default,WM,0,0,0,,If I save it instead of selling, I could make more money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.92,0:12:45.06,Default,Peasant,0,0,0,,Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.06,0:12:46.38,Default,Peasant,0,0,0,,Give me two bags!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.68,0:12:50.45,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Wheat prices have begun rising abnormally quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.79,0:12:52.63,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Sixty-four points over the normal average.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.63,0:12:54.67,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Nine more than last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.67,0:12:55.96,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Are the fast horses ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.96,0:12:57.24,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.71,0:12:59.96,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Now it's a matter of how fast we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.50,0:13:03.97,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Focus on selling these wheat purchase agreements
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.16,0:13:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to the larger landholders.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.29,0:13:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.71,0:13:09.83,Default,Account,0,0,0,,The three councilors who support
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.83,0:13:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the Central Church won't agree to any more wheat purchases.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.09,0:13:14.67,Default,Account,0,0,0,,Any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.67,0:13:17.90,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,The Black Hand will keep them out of the action
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.65,0:13:20.61,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,for two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.89,0:13:24.48,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Keep it quiet for as long as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.48,0:13:27.16,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,And then, we'll go all-out for two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.38,0:13:30.16,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,I shan't let them stop this lovely waltz.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.39,0:13:32.12,Default,Merchant Student,0,0,0,,A letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.75,0:13:35.50,Default,Merchant Student,0,0,0,,I haven't heard from him in ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.31,0:13:39.42,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hello. How have you been?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.21,0:13:43.74,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,{\i1}Things in the Holy Capital grow strange.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.09,0:13:48.14,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,{\i1}Grain prices, primarily wheat, are rapidly rising.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:52.01,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,{\i1}And it's causing a corresponding rise in the price of beans and even chestnuts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.56,0:13:56.66,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,{\i1}But since the landholders are obligated to sell at low prices,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.66,0:14:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}grain merchants and bakers are closing their doors for fear of bankruptcy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.71,0:14:05.99,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Howev{\i1}er, the landowners and nobility save their money.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.20,0:14:09.39,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,{\i1}And in some special way...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.69,0:14:13.45,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,Clearly, someone is behind this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.99,0:14:16.37,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,What are you seeing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.85,0:14:20.46,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,In the Central Nations, everything is increasing in price.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.96,0:14:23.49,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,No matter how much money nobles save,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.49,0:14:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it won't be enough to buy anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.39,0:14:30.01,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,We'll see prices continue to increase like nothing before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.69,0:14:34.53,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,To get what they need, they'll look to the Southern Triad
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.53,0:14:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,where prices haven't risen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.12,0:14:38.89,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,If we get involved...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.24,0:14:42.27,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,it'll destroy our country's economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.42,0:14:46.35,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,This is a serious problem we face!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.35,0:14:48.57,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,One wrong step, and we're doomed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.63,0:14:51.32,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,What are our options?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.91,0:14:54.20,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,First, we utilize tariffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.17,0:14:56.51,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,We levy a tax on many products,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.51,0:15:01.21,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,especially wheat, but only when they leave the Southern Triad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.03,0:15:05.23,Default,MSt,0,0,0,,Try to take out wheat or potatoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.23,0:15:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll tax ten gold per wagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.60,0:15:08.88,Default,AdvisorGuy,0,0,0,,Ten gold?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.35,0:15:10.38,Default,AdvisorGuy,0,0,0,,That's unheard of.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.66,0:15:15.43,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,Without it, the Central Nations will take all our food.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.43,0:15:18.93,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,We'll starve in the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.68,0:15:22.31,Default,Attendant,0,0,0,,Here it is. The summons...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.53,0:15:24.79,Default,Fat Lord,0,0,0,,We meet in two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.79,0:15:27.57,Default,Fat Lord,0,0,0,,The commanding general will be the Ashen King of the Fog Country.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.69,0:15:31.12,Default,Fat Lord,0,0,0,,Tell him we'll be there at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.12,0:15:31.74,Default,Attendant,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.92,0:15:34.11,Default,Fat Lord,0,0,0,,I have plenty of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.11,0:15:37.28,Default,Fat Lord,0,0,0,,If I buy 700... No, 1,000 mercenaries...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.28,0:15:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The High Priest will surely remember me if my forces outnumber the Ashen King's.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.74,0:15:45.61,Default,Fat Lord,0,0,0,,I could become a count!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.18,0:15:51.13,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Now, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.25,0:15:56.68,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,How will your Southern Triad respond?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.67,0:15:59.31,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,I expect great things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.28,0:16:17.41,Default,DP,0,0,0,,It warms me right up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.41,0:16:19.55,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,So, what brings you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.55,0:16:21.54,Default,DP,0,0,0,,I came to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.54,0:16:23.05,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,How did you find me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:24.67,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,The Hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:29.67,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,No, this is my own task, so I've kept it secret from my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.97,0:16:35.18,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,A passing mage used detection magic to tell me where you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.24,0:16:38.64,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,I can hear my sense of reality shattering.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.65,0:16:40.80,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.80,0:16:43.79,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,What do you require, Princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.79,0:16:44.99,Default,DP,0,0,0,,Salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.99,0:16:46.19,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.19,0:16:47.63,Default,DP,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.63,0:16:49.44,Default,DP,0,0,0,,As much as we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.44,0:16:51.65,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,That's a rather vague request.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.40,0:16:53.99,Default,DP,0,0,0,,Hence why I am here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.14,0:16:58.91,Default,DP,0,0,0,,Only you are able to fulfill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.47,0:17:01.91,Default,DP,0,0,0,,In the Demon Realm, salt is a valuable commodity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.15,0:17:04.49,Default,DP,0,0,0,,I'd like you to spare me some.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.52,0:17:12.52,Default,DP,0,0,0,,It warms me right down to my tail!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.65,0:17:17.70,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,It's seriously a miracle you weren't discovered on your way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.70,0:17:18.76,Default,DP,0,0,0,,My tail?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.63,0:17:20.51,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,And your horns.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.44,0:17:23.52,Default,DP,0,0,0,,Some were suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.00,0:17:29.31,Default,DP,0,0,0,,But as soon as I used my charms on them, they all let me go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:36.77,Default,Y,0,0,0,,The merchants may be the first to find
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.77,0:17:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,what cannot be expressed in loss and profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.06,0:17:47.29,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,You may be the one who'll lead me to that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.45,0:17:51.75,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,I think there's too much we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.79,0:17:53.76,Default,DP,0,0,0,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.05,0:17:56.46,Default,Ym,0,0,0,,About each other, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.18,0:18:06.27,Default,MH,0,0,0,,Master, are you really becoming the Demon King?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.12,0:18:08.27,Default,M,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.81,0:18:13.03,Default,HM,0,0,0,,Do you know what that entails?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.59,0:18:15.53,Default,HM,0,0,0,,You'll have to enter the Underworld Palace!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.15,0:18:19.95,Default,HM,0,0,0,,The Demon Kings of old will take over your mind and body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.21,0:18:22.88,Default,M,0,0,0,,They don't take it over, just alter it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.88,0:18:26.24,Default,M,0,0,0,,If they took it over, there could be a way to undo the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.24,0:18:28.16,Default,M,0,0,0,,But once complete, the alteration cannot be undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.16,0:18:29.83,Default,HM,0,0,0,,That's even worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.34,0:18:33.88,Default,M,0,0,0,,No... Even altered, I'm still myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.48,0:18:38.03,Default,M,0,0,0,,The sins I've committed will remain mine until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.03,0:18:39.76,Default,HM,0,0,0,,This all sounds like a bad thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.95,0:18:43.64,Default,M,0,0,0,,Don't worry. The alteration will take time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.21,0:18:47.04,Default,M,0,0,0,,So I'll just enter the Underworld Palace a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.04,0:18:48.14,Default,M,0,0,0,,and then I'll leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.31,0:18:51.65,Default,HM,0,0,0,,Then you won't get the Demon King's combat prowess.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.65,0:18:54.32,Default,HM,0,0,0,,How will you rule the Demon Realm that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.15,0:18:57.28,Default,M,0,0,0,,I won't use violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.16,0:18:59.74,Default,HM,0,0,0,,Then what'll you use?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.63,0:19:03.24,Default,M,0,0,0,,I wish to meet my fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.94,0:19:06.75,Default,M,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.79,0:19:15.80,Default,HM,0,0,0,,A human boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.24,0:19:17.63,Default,M,0,0,0,,He's the Hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.63,0:19:20.79,Default,M,0,0,0,,one of two key figures of our era.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.79,0:19:23.37,Default,M,0,0,0,,In about 15 years, he'll do great things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.01,0:19:27.81,Default,M,0,0,0,,I want to see him once he becomes the Hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.34,0:19:31.06,Default,HM,0,0,0,,He'll try to kill the Demon King!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.06,0:19:32.81,Default,M,0,0,0,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.59,0:19:39.91,Default,M,0,0,0,,To meet me, he'll come a long, long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.91,0:19:43.74,Default,M,0,0,0,,Of course, his sword may be meant to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.66,0:19:46.24,Default,M,0,0,0,,But before that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.24,0:19:48.41,Default,M,0,0,0,,{\fscx100\fscy100}I can at least say, "Hello."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.15,0:19:50.58,Default,M,0,0,0,,{\fscx106\fscy100}And if a miracle occurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.12,0:19:54.24,Default,M,0,0,0,,{\fscx97\fscy100}perhaps he'll let me touch his black hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.09,0:19:57.94,Default,M,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's very fluffy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.94,0:20:00.09,Default,M,0,0,0,,Running your hand through it must be pleasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.67,0:20:07.49,Default,HM,0,0,0,,You're mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.49,0:20:10.76,Default,M,0,0,0,,I think that this is my only chance
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.70,0:20:14.45,Default,M,0,0,0,,to bear witness to a future no one else has seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.45,0:20:17.80,Default,M,0,0,0,,to read a story beyond this library,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.99,0:20:20.65,Default,M,0,0,0,,and to meet my fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.81,0:20:28.79,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,This is an official declaration of war that arrived this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.39,0:20:32.90,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,The church has also sent a letter of excommunication.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.90,0:20:34.29,Default,Y,0,0,0,,That's too fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.29,0:20:37.17,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,Our tariffs meant that the grains
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.17,0:20:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,they relied upon were no longer available.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.95,0:20:44.30,Default,Wk,0,0,0,,This declaration of war is the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.46,0:20:46.68,Default,Y,0,0,0,,When will the war begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.27,0:20:50.72,Default,B,0,0,0,,The first month of winter, on the fourth day of the rabbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.72,0:20:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,upon the northern fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.10,0:20:53.19,Default,Y,0,0,0,,In ten days?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.71,0:20:57.39,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Dammit, I don't want to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.23,0:21:01.32,Default,Y,0,0,0,,This can't be what she wanted!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.32,0:21:02.87,Default,B,0,0,0,,Hero...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.87,0:21:05.32,Default,Y,0,0,0,,This can't be how it ends!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.92,0:21:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,God dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.57,0:21:09.83,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Why is she absent when I need her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.85,0:21:13.57,Default,M,0,0,0,,What's on the other side of the hill?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.57,0:21:15.73,Default,M,0,0,0,,That's what I want to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.73,0:21:19.69,Default,M,0,0,0,,If it's possible to end the war another way...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.48,0:21:23.48,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Winter King...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.73,0:21:29.30,Default,Y,0,0,0,,If a war begins, how long can we fight without casualties?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.29,0:21:31.84,Default,Y,0,0,0,,I don't want people to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.84,0:21:34.01,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Not on our side, or theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.59,0:21:37.25,Default,Y,0,0,0,,I'm not being naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.25,0:21:38.81,Default,Y,0,0,0,,It's absolutely necessary for what must happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.57,0:21:43.03,Default,WK,0,0,0,,It'll depend on the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.31,0:21:44.40,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Snow?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.39,0:21:46.64,Default,WK,0,0,0,,If we can last four weeks...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.25,0:21:50.91,Default,WK,0,0,0,,With winter coming, we might have snowfall two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.63,0:21:52.57,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Can you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.70,0:21:56.79,Default,WK,0,0,0,,I shall accept the task.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.48,0:22:00.34,Default,WK,0,0,0,,I swear by my name.
